  ('6-9m','6–9 months',6,9,true,'cluster_object_permanence','I’m finding hidden things',3,true,'cluster_object_permanence','Object permanence and hide-and-find play','Your baby may be starting to notice that things can disappear and come back. Peekaboo, scarves, boxes and drop-and-find games make that discovery feel fun. These little repeats can support memory, attention and early problem-solving in a very everyday way.','for_your_child','cat_peekaboo_scarf','Peekaboo scarves','Peekaboo Scarf',1,'Peekaboo can become especially fun when your baby starts noticing that people and objects come back. A soft scarf or play silk gives you an easy way to hide, reveal, laugh and repeat, while keeping fabric away during sleep. It keeps the play simple, recognisable and easy to repeat.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A more thoughtful idea beyond the obvious shelf.','If the family already owns something similar, choose this only if it adds a clearer age-fit challenge or easier everyday use.','Peekaboo scarves','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
