  ('6-9m','6–9 months',6,9,true,'cluster_mouth_sensory','I’m exploring with my mouth',5,true,'cluster_mouth_sensory','Mouthing, teething and sensory exploration','At this stage, mouthing is one way your baby explores shape, texture and comfort. Safe, easy-clean objects can give them something suitable to chew, hold and investigate. It also helps parents keep a clearer line between useful sensory play and risky household objects.','for_both','cat_teethers','Teethers and chew-safe toys','Teethers',1,'Mouthing is a normal way for babies to explore, and teething can make safe chewing feel soothing. Choose easy-clean, age-suitable teethers, check them often for wear, and be cautious with pre-loved items because hygiene matters. It gives families a calm, practical way to try it.','for_both','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A familiar gift that fits this stage well.','If you already have teethers, keep only easy-clean, age-fit pieces in good condition and retire anything damaged.','Teethers and chew-safe toys','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('6-9m','6–9 months',6,9,true,'cluster_mouth_sensory','I’m exploring with my mouth',5,true,'cluster_mouth_sensory','Mouthing, teething and sensory exploration','At this stage, mouthing is one way your baby explores shape, texture and comfort. Safe, easy-clean objects can give them something suitable to chew, hold and investigate. It also helps parents keep a clearer line between useful sensory play and risky household objects.','for_both','cat_texture_cards_books','Touch-and-feel cards or books','Texture Cards Books',2,'Texture cards and touch books let your baby feel, look and listen at the same time. Scratching, patting or mouthing a safe page can become a shared moment, while you add simple words for what they notice. It keeps the play simple, recognisable and easy to repeat.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A more thoughtful idea beyond the obvious shelf.','If books are already part of the day, look for a new reason to pause: faces, textures, gestures, rhythm or simple repetition.','Touch-and-feel cards or books','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
